						<summary>

						<p>Stone lying in a field known as Chinna Veṅkaṭādri-chēnu.</p>						

						<p>States that the field lying on the boundaries of the villages Peda-Jūṭūru and China-Jūṭūru is a gift to a <hi rend="italic">brāhmaṇa</hi> and a field to the engraver of the inscription, viz. Patevatōju. In characters of about the 16th century A.D.</p>						

